Business Brief -- American Travellers Corp.:
   Report of Flat Profit Sends
   Share Price Tumbling 16%
American Travellers, which provides individual insurance
for long-term health care, said net was $3.1 million, or 30
cents a share, compared with $3.1 million, or 31 cents a
share, a year earlier. Revenue was up 62% to $38 million from
$23.4 million.
   The results included a charge of $1,000,000 for settlement
of litigation involving two policy claims.
   American Travellers also restated its second-quarter
earnings to $2.6 million, or 25 cents a share, from $3.4
million, or 33 cents a share, and third-quarter earnings to
$2.9 million, or 28 cents a share, from $3.6 million, or 35
cents a share. It said the revisions were necessary "to
correct errors in recording certain expenses and acquisitions
completed in 1991."